<!--
    HOW OUTFITS ARE ADDED TO THIS WARDROBE
    =======================================
    Each <Outfit> defines a complete clothing combination that NPCs can wear at
    the tennis courts.  The game randomly picks one outfit per NPC per day.

    OverwearSets  – outer clothing only (top, skirt, shoes).  The game
                    automatically adds underwear from the character's personal
                    wardrobe or via random generation.  This is the preferred
                    section for tennis outfits.
    FullSets      – full outfit including underwear.  Used as a fallback when
                    the OverwearSet assembly path is not available.

    To add a new outfit:
      1. Copy an existing <Outfit> block inside the desired section.
      2. Change the "name" attribute to something unique and descriptive.
      3. Adjust colour values on each <Item>:
           red, green, blue  – main colour  (0.0–1.0)
           alpha             – opacity       (0.0–1.0, usually 0.95)
      4. Change the "name" attribute on <Item> to a valid clothing identifier
         from clothing_lists_ren.py.  Note the typo "Sleveless_Top" is correct.
      5. Optionally add pattern attributes:
           pattern           – e.g. "Pattern_1"
           pred, pgreen, pblue, palpha – pattern colour/opacity
      6. The wardrobe XML is reloaded on every save-load via the compatibility
         fix, so new outfits take effect immediately on existing saves.
-->
